You can view and manage asset replacements from two related lists on asset detail pages: Primary Assets and Related Assets.

To track an asset replacement, navigate to the record of the replaced asset. In the Primary Assets related list, click New Asset Relationship and select the new asset. Choose a relationship type and optionally enter dates if the new asset will only be in use for a certain amount of time. Save your changes.

This asset relationship now appears on both records, but subsequent replacements (such as replacing Door Model 2 with Door Model 3) won't appear on the original record.
title: Asset Replacement Tracking
